data.text:
KONE CENTENNIAL FOUNDATION ( KCF ) was founded in 2010 by KONE Corporation in celebration of its 100th anniversary. The Foundation continues to work in close cooperation with KONE Corporation, but it is independent from the company both juridically and operatively.

KCF projects are located only in countries where they are most needed and where local KONE units can contribute practical support. The Foundation welcomes volunteers who wish to contribute their time and skills to its projects.

KCF neither solicits grant proposals nor encourages unsolicited submissions. The Foundation may accept gifts and bequests from corporations and individuals.

CONTACT US

KONE CENTENNIAL FOUNDATION

Kartanontie 1

00330 Helsinki

Finland

If you are interested in learning more about KCF, send us a message, we will get back to you as soon as possible.

KINDLY NOTE THAT THE FOUNDATION DOES NOT CURRENTLY ACCEPT DONATION REQUESTS.
